Initial commit: Nexus AI web app (React + Vite + TS)

Standalone responsive web client that reuses the existing Nexus AI backend
(same-origin /api reverse proxy via nginx). Mirrors the Android app's
Expense, News, AI Tutor, Cloud, Settings and Login features.

- React 18 + Vite + TypeScript, Tailwind (dark/white themes), TanStack Query
  + Zustand, React Router with auth guard, Axios client with backoff retry.
- Self-hosted fonts (@fontsource) so blocked font CDNs can't affect the UI.
- Markdown sanitized (rehype-sanitize) against feed XSS; strict CSP + security
  headers in nginx.
- Resumable/chunked cloud upload for large files (8 MiB chunks, resume on drop,
  idempotent), client-log -> backend Telegram relay, JWT app-login support.
- Dockerfile: node build -> nginx (port 8080), runtime API_UPSTREAM via envsubst.
